A Class 7 seven pupil on Tuesday stabbed and killed his classmate with a kitchen knife following a fight over a pen at their school in Nyamira County. The boy aged 17 years is said to have engaged in a fight over ownership of a pen with his 14-year-old deskmate at Bogwendo Primary School before they separated by the teacher on duty. However, after lunch break the 17-year-old returned to school with a knife and stabbed his classmate on the chest, killing him on the spot. The accused attempted to escape and hide the knife but was arrested and detained at Sengera Police Station in Manga area. Sengera OCPD Gabriel Mwangangi confirmed the arrest, stating that investigations into the incident are underway. Following the incident irate locals stormed the boyâ€™s home and torched three houses belonging to their family. No one was injured as the family members managed to escape during the chaos. Also Read: The body of the deceased pupil was moved to the Nyamira Level V Hospital morgue. Video Of The Day: | SUCCESS AND AFTER | Tracking the progress made by students who topped KCSE in past years